#10200
Keywords:	dweller threshold
Name:	Dweller on the Threshold
RoomDesc:$
The Dweller on the Threshold hangs here 

~
LookDesc:$
It materializes from nowhere, as if it has always been here, beyond your
limited senses. It is hugh, fully filling your field of view. You attempt to
look at it directly but it is constantly shifting and changing, as if it
existed here and on multiple other dimensions simultaneously. For a moment it
appears to be a long lost friend, then a roaring dragon, then an amorphous
mass of eyes and tentacles, then something beyond even your ability to
comphrehend or describe! Regardless, you know this to be the Dweller on the
Threshold, the guardian of the entry to the Metaplanes. It speaks, or rather
you hear. ^W"You have chosen to travel here, beyond the realm of your kind. We
know of your quest and seen it's outcome. We know all that was, what is and
will come to pass but my not interfer. If you decide to continue, know
this...this place is not like any you have experienced thus far. Here, your
spirit can be injuried and it will be real, for here it the birthplace of all
realities. If you are wounded here, so shall your flesh in your reality. If
you die here, so shall your flesh decay in your reality. You quest for
enlightment and knowledge and power. These things are beyond our kin since we
have all, know all and are Power. Know this, if you continue from here, you
may not stop. All that is here is as real or more so than your home. If you
voluntarily return to your mortal existance, you will be forbidden entrance to
this place again for one cycle of the natural satelite of your home plane. If
you are injured and rendered unconcious or die, you will return to the dust
from whence you came and be forbidden entry for one rotation of your home
plane. A companion may aid you on this quest but doing so will lessen the
duration of your stay in the Metaplanes. Your guide to this place may
accompany you, but not aid you. Before continuing on your quest, you must
first face the Mirror and once successfully past this hurdle, on to the planes
you seek."^N 
~
